gurmukhi: Kylq kwnH so cMdRBgw kib sXwm khY rs jo aumihXo hY ] pRIq krI Aiq hI iqh so bhu logn ko auphws sihXo hY ]
transliteration: Khelat Kaahn So Channdrabhagad Kabi Syaam Kahai Ras Jo Oumhiyo Hai|| Preet Kariat(i) Hitih So Bahu Logad Ko Oup-haas Sahiyo Hai||
translation: A profound shower of pleasure was experienced, when Chandarbhaga and Krishna played together; these gopis in deep love for Krishna endured ridicules of many people;

gurmukhi: moiqn mwl FrI gr qy kib ny iqh ko js AYsy kihXo hY ] Awnn cMdR mno pRgtY Cip kY AMiDAwr pqwr gXo hY ]596]
transliteration: Motin Maal Dharigad Te Kabi Ne Tih Ko Jas Aise Bahiyo Hai|| Oonan Channdra Mano Pragtai Chhap(i) Kai Andiaar Pataar Gado Hai||596||
translation: The necklace of pearls has falled down from her neck and the poet says that it seems that on the manifestation of the moon-face, the darkness has concealed itself in the nether-world.596.

gurmukhi: guAwrn rUp inhwr kY ieau aupjXo ijX Bwv ] rwjq jXo mih cwNdnI kMjn sihq qlwv ]597]
transliteration: Gvaaran Roop Nihaar Kai Io Oupjyo Jiya Bhaav|| Raajat Jyo Maih Chaandanikanjan Sahit Talaav||597||
translation: Seeing the beauty of the gopis, it seems that the tank of lotus-flowers looks splendid in moon-lit night.597.

gurmukhi: locn hY ijn ky su pRBw Dr Awnn hY ijn ko sm mYnw ] kYkY ktwC curwie lXo mn pY iqn ko joaU r`Ck DYnw ]
transliteration: Lochanndhai Jin Ke Su Prabhaa Dhar Aanan Hai Jin Ko Sam Mainaa|| Kai-kai Kataachh Churaae Layo Man Pai Tin Ko Jooo Rachchhak Dhaeenaa||
translation: They, whose eyes are like lotus and the remaining body like the god of love, their mind has been stolen by Krishna the protector of cows, with signs;

gurmukhi: kyhir sI ijn kI kt hY su kpoq so kMT su koikl bYnw ] qwih lXo hir kY hir ko mn Bauh ncwie ncwie kY nYnw ]598]
transliteration: Kehar(i) Sijin Kikat Hai Su Kapot So Kanth Su Kokil Bainaa|| Taah(i) Layo Har(i) Kai Har(i) Ko Man Bhauh Nachaae Nachaae Kai Nainaa||598||
translation: They, whose waist is like that of a lion, the throat like that of a pigeon and the speech like that of a nightingale, their mind has been abducted by Krishna with signs of his eyebrows and eyes.598.

gurmukhi: kwnH ibrwjq gÍwrn mY kib sXwm khY ijn ko kCu Bau nw ] qwq kI bwq ko nYk sunY ijm ky sMg BRwq krXo bn gaunw ]
transliteration: Kaahn Biraajat Gvaaran Mai Kabi Syaam Kahai Jin Ko Kachh(u) Bhau Naa|| Taat Kibaat Ko Naik Sounai Jim Ke San Bhraat Daryo Ban Gadddaa||
translation: Krishna is seated amongst those gopis, who do not fear anyone; they are wandering with that Ram-like Krishna, who had gone to the forest with his brother on listening to the words of his father;

gurmukhi: qw kI ltY ltkY mo joaU swDn ky mn gXwn idvaunw ] sMdl pY aupjI aupmw mno lwg rhy Aihrwjn Caunw ]599]
transliteration: Taa Kilatai Latkai Mo Jooo Saadhan Ke Man Gyaan Divaounaa|| Sandal Pai Oupjioupmaa Mano Laag Rahe Aihraajan Chhaounaa||599||
translation: The locks of his hair; which even enlighten the saints with knowledge and they seem like the young ones of black serpents on the sandalwood.599.

gurmukhi: Kylq hY soaU gÍwrn mY joaU aUpr pIq Dryau praunw ] jo isr SqRn ky hirqw joaU swDn ko brdwn idvaunw ]
transliteration: Khelat Hai Sooo Gvaaran Mai Jooo Oopar Peet Ddareo Paraounaa|| Jo Sir Shatran Ke Haritaa Jooo Saadhan Ko Bardaan Divaounaa||
translation: He, who is wearing the yellow raiments, he is playing with the gopis; he is the destroyer of enemies and bestower of boons on the saints;

gurmukhi: bIc rhXo jg ky riv ky kib sXwm khY ijh kO pun Kaunw ] rwjq XO AlkY iqn kI mno cMdn lwg rhY Aih Caunw ]600]
transliteration: Beech Rahyo Jag Ke Rav(i) Ke Kabi Syaam Kahai Jih Kau Poun Khaounaa|| Raajat Yaoon Alkai Tin Kimano Channdan Laag Rahai Ah(i) Chhaounaa||600||
translation: He pervades all, in the world, sky, sun etc. and he is never destroyed; his locks of hair on his forehead look like the young ones of serpents hanging on the sandalwood tree.600.
